programme.title: Live NFL
programme.desc: Buffalo Bills v New England Patriots (Kick-off 12.15am). Coverage of the week eight match between the AFC East rivals, which comes from New Era Field. The Bills have struggled for consistency so far and face a tough task against last season's runners-up. The Patriots have made a solid, if unspectacular, start to the campaign as they look to go one better this time around and regain the Super Bowl title they claimed a year earlier. The sides last met in New England in week 16 of last term, with the Patriots prevailing 37-16.

programme.title: Live Carabao Cup
programme.desc: Burton Albion v Nottingham Forest (Kick-off 7.45pm). All the action from the fourth-round clash, taking place at the Pirelli Stadium. Burton recorded a shock 2-1 win over Premier League outfit Burnley in the previous round, while Forest also defeated top-flight opposition when they overcame Newcastle United 3-2 in round two. The sides drew 0-0 here in the Championship last term, with Albion failing to avenge a 2-0 defeat earlier in the season at the City Ground.
